<section class="content-section" id="overview-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">IT Software Payroll in Delhi: CTC, ESOPs, and Tech Compliance</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <p><strong>&#128204; TL;DR - IT Software Payroll in Delhi Services at a Glance</strong></p>
                    <p>IT payroll = CTC with variable pay (performance/retention/referral bonus) + ESOP perquisite S.17(2)(vi) in monthly TDS + PF 12%+12% (ESI only support staff - most devs above Rs 21K) + freelancer S.194J 10% + multi-state NCR (Delhi no PT / UP no PT / Haryana PT) + 50% basic rule + EOR for foreign IT. 7,000+ IT companies Delhi NCR. From Rs 5,000/month.</p>
                </div>
                <p>Delhi NCR is India's second-largest IT hub. For a comprehensive overview, see our <a href="/payroll-services-for-it-and-software-industry">IT Software Payroll</a> national guide.</p><div class="table-responsive-wrapper"><table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>ESOP</td><td>Perquisite = (FMV - Exercise price) × Shares. S.17(2)(vi). TDS in payroll. S.80-IAC deferral</td></tr><tr><td>Freelancer TDS</td><td>S.194J at 10% for devs/designers/consultants >Rs 30K/year. Alongside employee payroll</td></tr><tr><td>Statutory</td><td>PF 12%+12%. ESI only support staff (devs above Rs 21K). No PT in Delhi</td></tr><tr><td>Variable Pay</td><td>Performance bonus, retention bonus, referral. Quarterly/annual. Dynamic TDS</td></tr><tr><td>Cost From</td><td>Rs 5,000/month (startup); Rs 15,000-55,000 (mid-size to IT services)</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p</p>
                <p>Nehru Place/Jasola (Wipro, Accenture, IT services). Okhla (BPOs). CP/Barakhamba (IBM, SaaS startups). Dwarka/Rohini emerging tech. Noida (HCL, TCS) + Gurugram (Google, Microsoft). 7,000+ IT companies. CTC-heavy with 10-20% variable. ESOP common. Freelancers extensive. High turnover 20-30%. No PT saves Rs 5L/year for 200 employees vs Bengaluru/Pune. STPI Delhi. Patron Rohini.</p>
                <p>Content is reviewed quarterly for accuracy.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 3: WHAT IS GSTAT APPEAL FILING -->
<section class="content-section" id="what-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="column-content">
                <h2 class="section-title">What Are IT/Software Payroll Services?</h2>
                <div class="content-text what-is-definition">
                    
                    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> CTC-based salary processing for tech companies covering complex compensation (base, variable, ESOPs, bonuses), PF/ESI/TDS, freelancer/contractor payments with S.194J/194C, multi-state NCR, and Labour Code compliance.</p><p><strong>4 key differences:</strong> (1) CTC-heavy with quarterly/annual variable components; (2) Extensive freelancer use = dual TDS streams S.192 + S.194J; (3) Multi-state NCR (Delhi no PT, Haryana PT); (4) High mobility = PF transfer volumes.</p><p>See <a href="/payroll-processing-and-management-services">Payroll Services</a> for general payroll.</p>

                </div>
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <p><strong>Key Terms for IT Software Payroll in Delhi:</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>ESOP Perquisite S.17(2)(vi):</strong> (FMV - exercise price) × shares = added to salary month of exercise. TDS by employer. S.80-IAC deferral for eligible DPIIT startups.</p><p><strong>S.194J Freelancer TDS:</strong> 10% on professional fees to freelance developers/designers/consultants >Rs 30K/year. Form 16A. Not salary.</p><p><strong>Variable Pay:</strong> Performance bonus (quarterly/annual), retention, referral. Processed when declared. Dynamic TDS adjustment required.</p><p><strong>50% Basic Rule:</strong> IT CTCs with 30-40% basic must restructure. 200-employee company averaging Rs 12L CTC = Rs 30-50L additional annual PF.</p><p><strong>EOR:</strong> Employer of Record for foreign IT companies hiring Delhi developers without Indian entity. Full compliant payroll by Patron.</p>

                </div>
            </div>
